\f1\b Augustin-Louis Cauchy
\f0\b0  
\fs23\fsmilli11900 \cf2 (
\fs28 \cf4 1789-1857), French {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematician"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mathematician}}, engineer, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 physicist}} who made pioneering contributions to several branches of mathematics, including {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_analysis"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mathematical analysis}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuum_mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 continuum mechanics}}. \
He was one of the first to state and rigorously prove theorems of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calculus"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 calculus}}, rejecting the heuristic principle of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Generality_of_algebra"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 generality of algebra}} of earlier authors. He almost singlehandedly founded {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_analysis"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 complex analysis}} and the study of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permutation_group"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 permutation groups}} in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abstract_algebra"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 abstract algebra}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3 A profound mathematician, Cauchy had a great influence over his contemporaries and successors; {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Freudenthal"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Hans Freudenthal}} stated: "More concepts and theorems have been named for Cauchy than for any other mathematician (in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elasticity_(physics)"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 elasticity}} alone there are sixteen concepts and theorems named for Cauchy)."
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf2 \super \

\fs28 \cf4 \nosupersub Cauchy was a prolific writer; he wrote approximately eight hundred research articles and five complete textbooks on a variety of topics in the fields of mathematics and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_physics"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mathematical physics}}.\
\
Oggi \'e9 il compleanno del grandissimo Augustin Louis Cauchy, matematico, ingegnere e fisico francese che diede contributi fondamentali in svariate branche della matematica che comprendono analisi matematica, teoria delle probabilit\'e0 e meccanica del continuo. \'c9 stato il primo a enunciare e dimostrare rigorosamente un\'92innumerevole quantit\'e0 di teoremi e ha praticamente fondato da solo l\'92analisi complessa. \
Da grande pensatore qual era, ha profondamente influenzato i matematici che l\'92hanno succeduto: di lui si dice che ha dato il nome a tanti teoremi quanto mai nessuno prima di lui. \
